4. Execution of ſentence: To which motion theſe two Sluces ſhould be ſo opened, that all corruptions in perſons, things, actions, may be ſwept away out of Churches and Common Wealths. Eccleſ. 8.11. Becauſe ſentence againſt an evill work is not executed ſpeedily, therefore the heart of the ſons of men is fully ſet in them to do evill: Ergo, Let judgment run down as water, and righteouſneſs, &c. Tſedecha, from Tſadick, Diviſum, divided;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
Righteouſneſſe divides to each one his due portion, according to right proportion. Thus Solomon with his ſword divides true juſtice to the two mothers, and the ſword is ſtill Juſtices embleme. 2 King. 2.8. Eliſha with his mantle divides the waters, and paſſeth over ſafely: This diviſion is the author and compleater of our ſafeties.
